summary:
What was it like filming your last scene on Game of Thrones? Was it immediate tears or champagne and celebration?  I
 started to...
caption:
What was it like filming your last scene on Game of Thrones? Was it immediate tears or champagne and celebration?

I started to do a little speech, not because I’m a pretentious actor, but because every time we said goodbye to a character, David [Benioff] and Dan [Weiss], the show-runners would give us a gift and the crew would be around and everyone would stop and you’d sort of say a few words and it was really beautiful. I mean, I got three words in before I just completely broke down. You just hold it in and you’re holding it in and you’re holding it in, and then I just burst into tears like a complete idiot.

summary: I have always strongly disliked Catelyn Tully for she never made amends or admitted her folly for taking Tyrion.  That tipped...
body:
I have always strongly disliked Catelyn Tully for she never made amends or admitted her folly for taking Tyrion.  That tipped everything on it’s head when she decided to take justice into her own hands with no thought for what would happen in Kings Landing, with the loss of the Stark household, the execution of Ned, letting Jaime Lannister free, the Red Wedding.  

One could argue that Jaime set the tinder to the flame by pushing Bran out the window and you would be fair in saying that; but like Jaime, Catelyn’s actions were purely made with emotion without any foresight for the chain of events that would then occur by abducting Tyrion and taking him to the Eyrie for “Kings Justice”. Let’s not kid ourselves that her actions didn’t start the War of the Five Kings.

Nothing will convince me of that otherwise.

Edit:  Thanks Catelyn for putting the guilt trip and onus onto Robb to win at all costs because otherwise the entire line of Stark will be wiped out.  Good mothering skills there, seeing you fucked it up already.

body:
